Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, ~{5-6%mins}. Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}. Halve the @Burger Buns{2}. Toast the buns in your #toaster{}.

Once the beef has browned, stir in the @Beef Stock Paste{10%g}, @Tomato Ketchup{2%tbsp} and @Water{50%ml} (see pantry for both). Simmer, ~{1-2%mins}. Add a splash of water if needed.

Top your bun bases with the beef mince, cheese and @Burger Sauce{45%g} - as much as you'd like. Sandwich shut with the lids.

Serve the @Baby Leaf Mix{50%g} salad on the side. Drizzle with @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml}. Scatter over the @Pumpkin Seeds{15%g}. Enjoy!